# Pathway Summary

> **Dataset:** GSE147334 | **Tool:** DAVID KEGG | **Author:** Abeera Iftikhar | **May 2026**

---

## Overview

KEGG pathway enrichment was performed separately for upregulated (n=103) and
downregulated (n=132) DEGs using DAVID Bioinformatics. A total of **10 KEGG
pathways** were identified — 8 from upregulated and 2 from downregulated genes.

---

## Upregulated DEGs — 8 Pathways

| # | Pathway | Genes | FDR | Significant |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Systemic lupus erythematosus | 8 | 6.39×10⁻⁴ | ✅ FDR < 0.01 |
| 2 | Cornified envelope formation | 9 | 6.39×10⁻⁴ | ✅ FDR < 0.01 |
| 3 | Alcoholism | 8 | 1.50×10⁻³ | ✅ FDR < 0.01 |
| 4 | Neutrophil extracellular trap formation | 8 | 1.50×10⁻³ | ✅ FDR < 0.01 |
| 5 | Viral carcinogenesis | 7 | 1.29×10⁻² | ✅ FDR < 0.05 |
| 6 | Staphylococcus aureus infection | 4 | 3.10×10⁻¹ | — nominal |
| 7 | Estrogen signaling pathway | 4 | 5.96×10⁻¹ | — nominal |
| 8 | Necroptosis | 4 | 7.32×10⁻¹ | — nominal |

---

## Downregulated DEGs — 2 Pathways

| # | Pathway | Genes | p-value | Significant |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Growth hormone synthesis & action | 4 | 1.17×10⁻² | — nominal |
| 2 | Wnt signaling pathway | 4 | 2.98×10⁻² | — nominal |

> Neither downregulated pathway achieved Benjamini FDR < 0.05.
> Results are nominally significant — treat as hypothesis-generating.

